Dumisani Simelane’s Michael Jackson-themed performances started more than a decade ago. But recently, one Twitter user was so inspired by a video of Simelane dancing, that she started an unofficial campaign to promote a total stranger. eNCA’s Dasen Thathiah reports. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Umlazi in KwaZulu-Natal has its own Michael Jackson and the MJ impersonator has just become a Twitter sensation. A user was so blown away by Dumisani Simelane’s moves, she started a campaign to get him some recognition. Simelane’s Michael Jackson-themed performances started more than a decade ago. He was intrigued by the world-renowned artist. Simelane is hoping to moonwalk into as many venues as he can to keep MJ’s spirit alive. * eNCA’s Dasen Thathiah reports.